 :download: vt. To transfer data or (esp.) code from a far-away system
(especially a larger host system) over a digital communications link to a
nearby system (especially a smaller client system. Oppose {upload}.
Historical use of these terms was at one time associated with transfers from
large timesharing machines to PCs or peripherals (download) and vice-versa
(upload). The modern usage relative to the speaker (rather than as an
indicator of the size and role of the machines) evolved as machine categories
lost most of their former functional importance.